{
  "stem": "5644.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 127,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But I know what I've been told during the resistance.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 128,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That Iwanska's wife is either Jewish or half-Jewish.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 129,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That could be.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 129,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't want to--",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 130,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--state it as confirmed.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 130,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I heard those things.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 131,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Then they start to order to get in more Betar in and everything else to the organization.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 131,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But very slowly in the beginning.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 132,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In the ghetto-- not in the ghetto, but in the quarters, the Jewish quarters, they start to organize the Betar, and they start to do something about it to have an organization.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 132,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But that took them a long time to organize it--",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 133,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--to put them together.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 134,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A long time, I would say, took them a good one and a half year, from '39, to organize the group properly.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 135,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I've been told-- I knew only about five, six.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 135,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I knew much more.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 135,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But to me-- to me, we'd been split in five groups of five.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 135,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "A leader and four.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 135,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So we didn't know anything about the rest.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 135,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We shouldn't know anything about the rest.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 135,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But we knew--",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 136,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "For security reasons in case someone is caught.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 137,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 137,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Most probably-- yes.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 137,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I haven't been any-- I've been a soldier.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 138,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "One of the group.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 139,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In a matter of fact, I had been involved very early in 1941 or '40, end of '40, because my wife's-- Luba's-- brother was in the organization already.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 139,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that was the friend of my friend.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 139,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Then I did have two another friends, one [INAUDIBLE] Beckerman and [INAUDIBLE] Geller.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 139,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But this Geller is not to be mixed up with the Geller from ZOB, because that was two Gellers.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 139,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "One was in our organization, one Geller was in another organization.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 140,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Of Luba's brother?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 141,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 141,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Mayorek. ?]",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 142,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Mayor.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
